  "description": "Unlock Word's hidden power features that can transform your workflow. From mail merge to macros, these advanced tools will help you work smarter and faster.",
  "metadata": {
    "duration": "25 minutes",
    "difficulty": "Advanced",
    "prerequisites": ["intro", "formatting", "advanced"]
  },
  "sections": [
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": "Discover the hidden gems of Microsoft Word that will make you look like a power user! From mail merge to macros, these features will save you time and impress your colleagues."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "content": "Learning Objectives"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "data": {
        "type": "unordered",
        "items": [
          "Master mail merge for mass communications",
          "Create and use macros for automation",
          "Utilize advanced find and replace features",
          "Implement document protection and security",
          "Use advanced field codes and formulas"
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "content": "Mail Merge Mastery"
    },
    {
      "type": "subheading",
      "content": "Understanding Mail Merge"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": "Mail merge allows you to create personalized documents for multiple recipients automatically."
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "data": {
        "type": "unordered",
        "items": [
          "**Main Document**: Your template with placeholders",
          "**Data Source**: Excel spreadsheet or database with recipient info",
          "**Merge Fields**: Placeholders that get replaced with actual data",
          "**Output**: Personalized documents for each recipient"
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "subheading",
      "content": "Creating a Mail Merge"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "data": {
        "type": "ordered",
        "items": [
          "Create your main document with merge fields",
          "Go to **Mailings** tab > **Start Mail Merge**",
          "Select **Step by Step Mail Merge Wizard**",
          "Choose document type (letters, emails, labels)",
          "Select recipients from existing list or create new",
          "Insert merge fields where you want personalized data",
          "Preview and complete the merge"
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "content": "Macros and Automation"
    },
    {
      "type": "subheading",
      "content": "Recording Macros"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": "Automate repetitive tasks by recording your actions as macros."
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "data": {
        "type": "ordered",
        "items": [
          "Go to **View** tab > **Macros** > **Record Macro**",
          "Name your macro and assign a shortcut key",
          "Perform the actions you want to automate",
          "Click **Stop Recording** when finished",
          "Test your macro with the assigned shortcut"
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "subheading",
      "content": "Common Macro Uses"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "data": {
        "type": "unordered",
        "items": [
          "**Format documents** with consistent styling",
          "**Insert frequently used text** or signatures",
          "**Apply complex formatting** sequences",
          "**Clean up imported text** from other sources",
          "**Generate reports** with specific formatting"
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "content": "Advanced Find and Replace"
    },
    {
      "type": "subheading",
      "content": "Using Wildcards and Patterns"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": "Go beyond simple find and replace with powerful pattern matching."
    },
    {
      "type": "table",
      "data": {
        "headers": ["Wildcard", "Description", "Example"],
        "rows": [
          ["**?**", "Any single character", "c?t finds cat, cut, cot"],
          ["*****", "Any number of characters", "s*d finds sad, said, started"],
          ["**[abc]**", "Any character in brackets", "[aeiou] finds any vowel"],
          ["**[!abc]**", "Any character NOT in brackets", "[!aeiou] finds consonants"],
          ["**{n}**", "Exactly n occurrences", "a{3} finds aaa"]
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "subheading",
      "content": "Find and Replace with Formatting"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": "Find and replace not just text, but also formatting and styles."
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "data": {
        "type": "unordered",
        "items": [
          "**Find specific formatting** (bold, italic, font size)",
          "**Replace formatting** without changing text",
          "**Find and replace styles** throughout document",
          "**Use special characters** (paragraph marks, tabs)",
          "**Apply formatting** to found text"
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "content": "Document Protection and Security"
    },
    {
      "type": "subheading",
      "content": "Restricting Editing"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": "Control who can edit your documents and what changes they can make."
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "data": {
        "type": "unordered",
        "items": [
          "**Read-only**: No changes allowed",
          "**Comments only**: Can add comments but not edit text",
          "**Tracked changes**: Can edit but changes are tracked",
          "**Filling forms**: Can only fill in form fields",
          "**No changes**: Completely locked document"
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "subheading",
      "content": "Password Protection"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "data": {
        "type": "ordered",
        "items": [
          "Go to **File** > **Info** > **Protect Document**",
          "Choose **Encrypt with Password**",
          "Enter a strong password",
          "Confirm the password",
          "Save the document"
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "content": "Advanced Field Codes"
    },
    {
      "type": "subheading",
      "content": "Using Field Codes"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": "Field codes provide dynamic content that updates automatically."
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "data": {
        "type": "unordered",
        "items": [
          "**Date and Time**: Current date, creation date, last saved",
          "**Document Information**: Title, author, file size",
          "**Calculations**: Simple math operations",
          "**Cross-references**: Links to headings, figures, tables",
          "**Conditional content**: Show/hide based on conditions"
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "subheading",
      "content": "Inserting Field Codes"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "data": {
        "type": "ordered",
        "items": [
          "Press **Ctrl + F9** to insert field braces",
          "Type the field name inside braces",
          "Add any switches or parameters",
          "Press **F9** to update the field",
          "Press **Alt + F9** to toggle field code view"
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "content": "Practice Exercise"
    },
    {
      "type": "exercise",
      "data": {
        "title": "Create a Mail Merge Campaign",
        "description": "Practice mail merge by creating a personalized email campaign for a fictional company.",
        "steps": [
          "Create a main document with merge fields",
          "Set up a data source with recipient information",
          "Insert appropriate merge fields",
          "Preview the merged documents",
          "Complete the merge and save results"
        ],
        "checklist": [
          "Main document has proper merge fields",
          "Data source contains all necessary information",
          "Merge fields are correctly formatted",
          "Preview shows personalized content",
          "Final documents are properly formatted"
        ],
        "estimatedTime": "15 minutes",
        "difficulty": "advanced"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "content": "Best Practices"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "data": {
        "type": "ordered",
        "items": [
          "**Test macros** in a copy of your document first",
          "**Use descriptive names** for macros and merge fields",
          "**Backup important documents** before running automation",
          "**Document your processes** for team consistency",
          "**Keep security in mind** when sharing protected documents"
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "tip",
      "content": "Use **Quick Parts** to save frequently used content like signatures, disclaimers, or standard paragraphs for quick insertion."
    }
  ]
} 